http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/Odisha-bid-to-promote-start-ups/article14005972.ece

Chief Minister Naveen Patnaik on Monday expressed hope that Odisha will remain among the top three States in the country in growth of start-ups within a period of two years.Mr. Patnaik said this after he held discussions with a high-level delegation from TiE Silicon Valley (TiE SV), a non-profit association dedicated to fostering entrepreneurship globally.The Chief Minister informed the delegation that the Odisha government will soon introduce a special policy to foster the growth of start-ups. The Industrial Promotion & Investment Corporation of Odisha Limited (IPICOL) has already signed a memorandum of understanding with TiE SV.The association is expected to significantly strengthen the incubation and start-up ecosystem in the State in the coming two to three years, according to a release issued by the IPICOL. During their two-day visit, the delegation will participate in a discussion on the proposed policy.The delegation will also meet some start-ups to discuss their business plans.